main event: Radar sighting of an unidentified object in the North Atlantic on 18 April 1948.
interesting points: The sighting was classified as radar contact at 1500 GMT, suggesting a speed of approximately 20 mph at an altitude of 11,000 ft., The object was evaluated as likely being birds, but no astronomical explanation was found probable., The first contact was made visually at a distance of 6000 yards., The radar target was tracked to a distance of 18,000 yards without any surface radar indications., The phenomenon was documented by the Coast Guard and reported for further analysis.
location: North Atlantic, Unknown Region, Unknown Country
